{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780929520582,"sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_mJUgGphm3bgbj6DbmRzX93wm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts","offset":280,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n280:       [keepId, supersededId],\n281:     );\n282: \n283:     // Repoint any relations targeting the superseded memory.\n284:     // Delete rows that would collide on the unique constraint before updating.\n285:     db.run(\n286:       `DELETE FROM memory_relations\n287:        WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?\n288:          AND EXISTS (\n289:            SELECT 1 FROM memory_relations r2\n290:            WHERE r2.target_memory_id = ?\n291:              AND r2.source_memory_id = memory_relations.source_memory_id\n292:              AND r2.relationship_type = memory_relations.relationship_type\n293:          )`,\n294:       [supersededId, keepId, keepId],\n295:     );\n296:     db.run(\n297:       `UPDATE memory_relations SET target_memory_id = ?\n298:        WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?`,\n299:       [keepId, supersededId, keepId],\n300:     );\n301:     db.run(\n302:       `DELETE FROM memory_relations\n303:        WHERE source_memory_id = ? AND target_memory_id != ?\n304:          AND EXISTS (\n305:            SELECT 1 FROM memory_relations r2\n306:            WHERE r2.source_memory_id = ?\n307:              AND r2.target_memory_id = memory_relations.target_memory_id\n308:              AND r2.relationship_type = memory_relations.relationship_type\n309:          )`,\n310:       [supersededId, keepId, keepId],\n311:     );\n312:     db.run(\n313:       `UPDATE memory_relations SET source_memory_id = ?\n314:        WHERE source_memory_id = ? AND target_memory_id != ?`,\n315:       [keepId, supersededId, keepId],\n316:     );\n317: \n318:     // Repoint context_items\n319:     db.run(\n320:       \"UPDATE context_items SET memory_id = ? WHERE memory_id = ?\",\n321:       [keepId, supersededId],\n322:     );\n323: \n324:     // Boost confidence of kept memory\n325:     db.run(\n326:       `UPDATE memories SET confidence = MIN(1.0, confidence + 0.1),\n327:        confirm_count = confirm_count + 1,\n328:        last_confirmed_at = datetime('now')\n329:        WHERE id = ?`,\n330:       [keepId],\n331:     );\n332:   })();\n333: }\n\n(End of file - total 333 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      [keepId, supersededId],\n    );\n\n    // Repoint any relations targeting the superseded memory.\n    // Delete rows that would collide on the unique constraint before updating.\n    db.run(\n      `DELETE FROM memory_relations\n       WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?\n         AND EXISTS (\n           SELECT 1 FROM memory_relations r2\n           WHERE r2.target_memory_id = ?\n             AND r2.source_memory_id = memory_relations.source_memory_id\n             AND r2.relationship_type = memory_relations.relationship_type\n         )`,\n      [supersededId, keepId, keepId],\n    );\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memory_relations SET target_memory_id = ?\n       WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?`,\n      [keepId, supersededId, keepId],","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts","text":"      [keepId, supersededId],\n    );\n\n    // Repoint any relations targeting the superseded memory.\n    // Delete rows that would collide on the unique constraint before updating.\n    db.run(\n      `DELETE FROM memory_relations\n       WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?\n         AND EXISTS (\n           SELECT 1 FROM memory_relations r2\n           WHERE r2.target_memory_id = ?\n             AND r2.source_memory_id = memory_relations.source_memory_id\n             AND r2.relationship_type = memory_relations.relationship_type\n         )`,\n      [supersededId, keepId, keepId],\n    );\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memory_relations SET target_memory_id = ?\n       WHERE target_memory_id = ? AND source_memory_id != ?`,\n      [keepId, supersededId, keepId],\n    );\n    db.run(\n      `DELETE FROM memory_relations\n       WHERE source_memory_id = ? AND target_memory_id != ?\n         AND EXISTS (\n           SELECT 1 FROM memory_relations r2\n           WHERE r2.source_memory_id = ?\n             AND r2.target_memory_id = memory_relations.target_memory_id\n             AND r2.relationship_type = memory_relations.relationship_type\n         )`,\n      [supersededId, keepId, keepId],\n    );\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memory_relations SET source_memory_id = ?\n       WHERE source_memory_id = ? AND target_memory_id != ?`,\n      [keepId, supersededId, keepId],\n    );\n\n    // Repoint context_items\n    db.run(\n      \"UPDATE context_items SET memory_id = ? WHERE memory_id = ?\",\n      [keepId, supersededId],\n    );\n\n    // Boost confidence of kept memory\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memories SET confidence = MIN(1.0, confidence + 0.1),\n       confirm_count = confirm_count + 1,\n       last_confirmed_at = datetime('now')\n       WHERE id = ?`,\n      [keepId],\n    );\n  })();\n}","lineStart":280,"lineEnd":333,"totalLines":333,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts","time":{"start":1780929520561,"end":1780929520579}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00762ee5d2247118016a26d3ef3f0081968d4b55b81a336903"}},"id":"prt_ea7abded2001II2nveiZBhHeJc","sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","messageID":"msg_ea7abcdeb001JGv7Ml8isuOPT4"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780929520985,"sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","part":{"id":"prt_ea7abe556001H5FHfvlsZEB7Ar","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"c8f81b4ac6325f3c1fc07eb2fde92d4663ce35b0","messageID":"msg_ea7abcdeb001JGv7Ml8isuOPT4","sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":110987,"input":1835,"output":77,"reasoning":19,"cache":{"write":0,"read":109056}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780929525247,"sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","part":{"id":"prt_ea7abf5f7001d0fubXu21H0x7e","messageID":"msg_ea7abe68f001P3f7W30Q7Vn4zS","sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","snapshot":"2346ef332f32a1708d1a6ce4fd58936128761fe3","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780929591875,"sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","part":{"id":"prt_ea7ac8782001urmMnp4jlnVMNY","messageID":"msg_ea7abe68f001P3f7W30Q7Vn4zS","sessionID":"ses_15858491bffeXJMuegc5mX6JyJ","type":"text","text":"## Mechanism\n\nOpenLTM’s authoritative memory unit is a DB row: `memories` stores `id`, `content`, `title`, confidence, status, and recall metadata, while `context_items` are also rows and explicitly “replace” per-project markdown context files (`packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:17`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:35`). Its lexical index is a derived FTS5 surface over those rows: `memories_fts` and `context_items_fts` are external-content FTS tables tied to rowids, with insert/delete/update triggers that mirror base-table changes (`packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:127`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:129`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:136`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:147`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:155`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:174`). Migration 020 shows the rebuild pattern: drop/recreate FTS, repopulate from base rows, then recreate triggers (`migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:7`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:16`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:20`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:24`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:43`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:50`).\n\nEmbeddings are row-keyed. Migration 010 splits vectors into `memory_embeddings(memory_id, embedding, model, dim, created_at)` with no verified content fingerprint (`migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:5`, `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:6`, `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:8`). Backfill detects only active rows with no embedding row (`packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:63`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:69`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:71`). New `learn()` inserts enqueue/inline embedding by memory id (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:352`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:396`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:401`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:403`), and the queue payload is only `{ memoryId }` (`packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:18`, `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:35`, `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/worker.ts:54`). This is insertion/missing-row freshness, not edited-document freshness. VERIFIED content edit paths update `memories.content` but do not show embedding invalidation in the same block (`src/graph-server.ts:1123`, `src/graph-server.ts:1124`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts:255`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/dedup.ts:258`); UNKNOWN whether another path re-embeds afterward.\n\nThe stronger transferable signal is that derived vector surfaces are rebuildable from an embedding source table and model/dim are treated as compatibility boundaries: `setEmbedding()` stores model/dim and dual-writes vec when available (`packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:36`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:45`), while `rebuildVecIndex()` rebuilds from `memory_embeddings` filtered by active dim/model (`packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:107`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:119`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:123`).\n\n## Storage-fit teachings for system-spec-kit (doc-based)\n\n- **Claim** · Keep FTS5 synchronized with the derived index row using insert/update/delete triggers, but treat filesystem scanning as the separate doc-freshness step · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:129`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:147`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:2675` · **Storage-fit** · TRANSFERS · **Maps-to** · index · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.92 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · n/a\n\n- **Claim** · FTS coverage migrations should rebuild from the base index table before re-enabling triggers · **Evidence** · `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:7`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:17`, `migrations/020_fts_coverage.sql:24` · **Storage-fit** · TRANSFERS · **Maps-to** · index / MCP · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.90 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · n/a\n\n- **Claim** · Missing-embedding backfill is insufficient for edited markdown; doc systems need per-doc content fingerprints that force re-index/re-embed when content changes · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:69`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:71`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/incremental-index.ts:173`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/incremental-index.ts:213` · **Storage-fit** · DOC-ANALOG · **Maps-to** · spec docs / index / memory_index_scan · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · HIGH · **Confidence** · 0.94 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · key freshness by canonical path + anchor + content_hash, not by row existence\n\n- **Claim** · Store model/dim with embeddings, but do not key reusable vectors solely by memory row id · **Evidence** · `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:6`, `migrations/010_memory_embeddings_split.sql:8`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-store.ts:485`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-store.ts:493` · **Storage-fit** · DOC-ANALOG · **Maps-to** · index / vector store · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.91 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · key cache entries by content_hash + embedder profile + input kind + model + dimensions\n\n- **Claim** · Make ANN/vector surfaces rebuildable and reconcilable from authoritative embedding storage after provider/model/dim changes · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:107`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:119`, `packages/openltm-core/src/vec/index.ts:146`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/embedders/embedding-reconcile.ts:160` · **Storage-fit** · TRANSFERS · **Maps-to** · MCP / memory_embedding_reconcile · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.88 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · n/a\n\n- **Claim** · Async embedding workers transfer only if jobs carry or validate the document version they embed · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:18`, `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:35`, `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/worker.ts:54` · **Storage-fit** · DOC-ANALOG · **Maps-to** · index / MCP · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.86 · **Re-shaping needed (if DOC-ANALOG)** · include canonical path, anchor, row id, and content_hash; discard stale jobs when current hash differs\n\n## Row-coupled findings (negative knowledge)\n\n- OpenLTM’s `learn()` reinforcement path updates `confirm_count` and confidence for an existing `dedup_key`; that is row lifecycle, not authored-doc freshness (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:317`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:321`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:324`).\n\n- “Needs embedding” equals “no `memory_embeddings` row”; edited docs can have an existing but stale vector, so this should not be ported as-is (`packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:63`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/embeddings.ts:69`).\n\n- Embedding jobs keyed only by `memoryId` are insertion-row coupled; doc systems need versioned jobs keyed to the edited document snapshot (`packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:18`, `packages/openltm-core/src/queue/index.ts:40`).\n\n- `context_items` as rows replacing markdown context files is anti-fit for system-spec-kit, where markdown continuity docs remain source of truth (`packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:17`).\n\n## Open questions\n\n- UNKNOWN whether OpenLTM has any hidden post-update hook that deletes/requeues embeddings after `memories.content` edits; the verified edit paths did not show one.\n\n- Should system-spec-kit’s FTS update trigger remain broad on every `memory_index` update, or become column-restricted to reduce churn for metadata-only changes?\n\n- Should `memory_index_scan` expose a clearer “hash changed → re-embedded/replaced” freshness audit line for edited authored docs?","time":{"start":1780929562498,"end":1780929591864},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0618ab2f2b20aad8016a26d41a785081919f01509b4154c488","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
